title: Grateful Dead Live at Frost Amphitheatre on 1982-10-10
description:
Set 1

Minglewood Blues-> Sugaree-> Little Red Rooster, Tennessee Jed, Cassidy, Loser, Far From Me, Looks Like Rain-> China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider

Set 2

Playin' In The Band-> Crazy Fingers-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Touch Of Gray-> Drums-> The Wheel-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away-> Black Peter-> Sugar Magnolia, E:Satisfaction-> E: It's All Over Now Baby Blue

reviews.review_text:
Hunter's Trix Another stellar matrix by Mr. Seamons. The Miller SBD is incredible for this show, especially considering the generally bad SBD recordings of this year (Phil is always buried in the mix, levels suck, etc.), but I find it a little too 'boomy' and thick. Hunter cures this ill by layering on a little AUD thinness to even things out. There are quite a few shows now where the Seamons matrix is the best sounding version. Thanks for the hard work man!

This is definitely one of the best shows from the early Brent era. One of the best "Cassidy" jams you will hear, and a great "Tennessee Jed." Jerry's voice is a little ragged, but overall, a five star performance and Hunter-ized tape.

Great Stuff Just getting into it after finding it on www.gratefuldeadoftheday.com - great mix here from on the matrix - you can really hear Phil in that Minglewood - Jerry et al are killing the Sugaree - looking forward to making my way through the rest - enjoy this nug

So many thanks to Hunter Seamons, great show great matrix I was in attendance on this lovely fall day.  The show impressed in person and the FOB audience from the mixing platform tape reconfirmed it time and time again.  

How can I thank Hunter Seamons for this magnificant matrix version.  It is outstanding.  

Enjoy it, especially Sugaree, Tenn. Jed, China/Rider, and a great second set, especially the Playin In the Band.
Band is ON big time, recording is beautiful! That's all! The music is playing the band here clearly.
My First Shows! I admittedly came along late in the game, but the two shows from this weekend blow me away to this day.  Great freakin' work, Hunter S.  These sound perfect!!

Good Show Amazing matrix recording!  You seriously feel like you were in attendance.

This is a good show, particularly for the stellar China - Rider.  Give it a shot!

Good recording and great playing This show was recommended to me and I'm glad for the recommendation. Excellent sound, the matrix really works well and the band are playing wonderfully. Jerry and Brent sound inspired here especially.
